With this background, the former Friska Vilijor (Sweden) and Nam Dinh (Vietnam) player is adamant Kenyan footballers have as much a chance of succeeding on the big stage as their counterparts in Europe, Asia, South America, and even North AfricaTo further hammer home the point on talent development, Sunguti has founded the Syokimau Academy in Nairobi, where he concentrates on training 100 youngsters aged between 9 and 17Sunguti's academy has since featured at an international tournament in Spain and was primed to Austria for another exposure trip this year before the coronavirus struck